
Overview of adj crazy

The adj crazy has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (10) brainsick, crazy, demented, disturbed, mad, sick, unbalanced, unhinged -- (affected with madness or insanity; "a man who had gone mad")
2. (2) crazy, half-baked, screwball, softheaded -- (foolish; totally unsound; "a crazy scheme"; "half-baked ideas"; "a screwball proposal without a prayer of working")
3. (1) crazy -- (possessed by inordinate excitement; "the crowd went crazy"; "was crazy to try his new bicycle")
4. crazy -- (bizarre or fantastic; "had a crazy dream"; "wore a crazy hat")
5. crazy, wild, dotty, gaga -- (intensely enthusiastic about or preoccupied with; "crazy about cars and racing"; "he is potty about her")
